==Introduction==
A '''Pivot Table Layout''' renders group of components using the following rules:
* every component of the group creates a new Column in the Table
* a component label is used as a Column Label (the content of the first Row of a Column; in bold)
* a component content (e.g. property value) is rendered in the second Row of a Column
* if a component is another embedded Group, it will be rendered as another embeded Pivot Table in the second Row of a Column (assuming that not other style was re-defined for that group)


==Definition==
<pre>
<concept>
  <structure layout="pivottable">
    <property name="Property 1">          <!-- first column  ->
    <property name="Property 2">          <!-- second column ->
    <property name="Property 3">          <!-- third column  ->
  <structure>
</concept>
</concept>
</pre>


==Example==
<pre>
<concept name="User" plural="Users" type="Dynamic" image="User.png" color="f9f9f9">
  <description></description>
  <structure layout="pivottable">
    <group name="Name" layout="table">
      <property name="Prefix" />
      <property name="First name" mandatory="true" />
      <property name="Last name" mandatory="true" />
    </group>
    <group name="Organization">
      <property name="Organization"/>
      <property name="Function"/>
      <property name="Address"/>
    </group>
    <group name="Contact information">
      <property name="Telephone"/>
      <property name="Email"/>
    </group>
    <property name="Remarks"/>
  </structure>
</concept>
</pre>


